<h2>Icon nsw-colors</h2>
<p>By default all nsw icons are distinctly nsw blue, there are some preset nsw-colors defined for icons though:</p>

<div class="ds-example">
  <svg class="nsw-icon nsw-icon--error" focusable="false" aria-hidden="true">
    <use xlink:href="#status-error"></use>
  </svg>
  <svg class="nsw-icon nsw-icon--success" focusable="false" aria-hidden="true">
    <use xlink:href="#status-success"></use>
  </svg>
  <svg class="nsw-icon nsw-icon--info" focusable="false" aria-hidden="true">
    <use xlink:href="#status-info"></use>
  </svg>
  <svg class="nsw-icon nsw-icon--warning" focusable="false" aria-hidden="true">
    <use xlink:href="#status-warning"></use>
  </svg>
</div>
<pre><code class="language-css">.nsw-icon--error
.nsw-icon--success
.nsw-icon--info
.nsw-icon--warning</code></pre>

<h2>Icon rotation</h2>
<p>By default nsw icon if directional will all point right, if another direction is needed helper classes can be applied to change the direction</p>
<div class="ds-example">
  <svg class="nsw-icon" focusable="false" aria-hidden="true">
    <use xlink:href="#chevron"></use>
  </svg>
  <svg class="nsw-icon nsw-icon--rotate-90" focusable="false" aria-hidden="true">
    <use xlink:href="#chevron"></use>
  </svg>
  <svg class="nsw-icon nsw-icon--rotate-180" focusable="false" aria-hidden="true">
    <use xlink:href="#chevron"></use>
  </svg>
  <svg class="nsw-icon nsw-icon--rotate-270" focusable="false" aria-hidden="true">
    <use xlink:href="#chevron"></use>
  </svg>
</div>

<pre><code class="language-css">.nsw-icon--rotate-90
.nsw-icon--rotate--180
.nsw-icon--rotate--270</code></pre>